00:44:02.891 --> 00:44:03.390
I believe.

00:44:03.390 --> 00:44:06.750
And the next one will cut
that significantly down

00:44:06.750 --> 00:44:08.670
below five kilograms.

00:44:08.670 --> 00:44:12.730
AUDIENCE: And are you worried,
as a possible perverse outcome

00:44:12.730 --> 00:44:14.332
of this, that people
will burn wood

00:44:14.332 --> 00:44:15.790
that they otherwise
would not have,

00:44:15.790 --> 00:44:17.195
just to charge their phone?

00:44:17.195 --> 00:44:18.820
RYAN GIST: That's
definitely a concern.

00:44:18.820 --> 00:44:21.860
I know Ethan and his team
have looked into that.

00:44:21.860 --> 00:44:23.260
ETHAN KAY: So, yeah.

00:44:23.260 --> 00:44:25.230
This was an initial
concern of ours.

00:44:25.230 --> 00:44:28.390
And after several
years of operations,

00:44:28.390 --> 00:44:30.400
not only have we never
seen that happen,

00:44:30.400 --> 00:44:40.000
but there is a PhD student at
Lawrence Berkeley Lab named

00:44:40.000 --> 00:44:45.580
Danny Wilson who did an
independent evaluation where

00:44:45.580 --> 00:44:49.630
he designed a stove
usage monitoring system.

00:44:49.630 --> 00:44:51.820
It was actually
to our camp stove,

00:44:51.820 --> 00:44:56.050
which is a product that wasn't
even designed for this market.

00:44:56.050 --> 00:44:58.400
And he looked at
whether people are

00:44:58.400 --> 00:45:03.270
using a camp stove for
charging and not for cooking.

00:45:03.270 --> 00:45:05.860
And again, that product
wasn't even designed

00:45:05.860 --> 00:45:08.170
for cooking in that market.

00:45:08.170 --> 00:45:12.870
And what he found was not only
were people not using the stove

00:45:12.870 --> 00:45:14.640
just for charging.

00:45:14.640 --> 00:45:18.070
The version of the
stove that had charging,

00:45:18.070 --> 00:45:21.190
households were using
it way more for cooking.

00:45:21.190 --> 00:45:25.190
So the inclusion of the
electricity generation

00:45:25.190 --> 00:45:29.120
actually increased
usage for cooking,

00:45:29.120 --> 00:45:31.100
while they were
co-generating power,

00:45:31.100 --> 00:45:34.320
but did not have the perverse
effect of customers using it

00:45:34.320 --> 00:45:37.050
just for charging.

